import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Conv1D, MaxPooling1D, Flatten, Dense
import numpy as np
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_percentage_error, r2_score,mean_absolute_error

# Data
data = pd.read_csv('/Users/aliabouyahia/Downloads/Data/AAPL-Daily.csv') 

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Extract features and target + normalisation for CNN
features = data[['Open', 'High', 'Low']].values
target = data[['Close']].shift(-1).fillna(method='ffill').values  # Predict the next day's close , null values are filled using forward filling method 

scaler_features = MinMaxScaler()
scaler_target = MinMaxScaler()
features_scaled = scaler_features.fit_transform(features)
target_scaled = scaler_target.fit_transform(target)

# Create time series dataset
def create_dataset(a, b, time_steps=1):
    X, Y = [], []
    for i in range(len(a) - time_steps):
        X.append(a[i:i + time_steps])
        Y.append(b[i + time_steps])
    return np.array(X), np.array(Y)

time_steps = 100 # Time steps for each sample 
a, b = create_dataset(features_scaled, target_scaled, time_steps)

# Split data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(a, b, test_size=0.2, shuffle=False)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Build the CNN model
model = Sequential([
    Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=3, activation='relu', input_shape=(time_steps, X.shape[2])),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=3, activation='relu'),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Flatten(),
    Dense(50, activation='relu'),
    Dense(1) 
])

model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Training and evaluation
history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_split=0.1, verbose=1)

# Make predictions
predictions = model.predict(X_test)

# Inverse transform the predictions and targets for comparison
Predicted_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(predictions)
Actual_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(y_test)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(Actual_Values, color ='blue',label='Actual Close Price')
plt.plot(Predicted_Values, color ='red',label='Predicted Close Price')
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel('AAPL Closing Price')
plt.legend()
plt.title('AAPL Closing Price Prediction (Daily Data)')
plt.show()
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Metrics Evaluation
mae = mean_absolute_error(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
mape = mean_absolute_percentage_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values)
r2_Score = r2_score(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
rmse =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values))

metrics = {
    'Metric': ['Mean Absolute Error', 'Root Mean Squared Error', 'Mean Absolute Percentage Error', 'R2 Score'],
    'Value': [f'{mae:.2f}', f'{rmse:.2f}', f'{(mape*100):.2f}%', f'{r2_Score:.2f}']
}
metrics_Table = pd.DataFrame(metrics)
print(metrics_Table)

# Data
data = pd.read_csv('/Users/aliabouyahia/Downloads/Data/AMZN-Daily.csv') 

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Extract features and target + normalisation for CNN
features = data[['Open', 'High', 'Low']].values
target = data[['Close']].shift(-1).fillna(method='ffill').values  # Predict the next day's close , null values are filled using forward filling method 

scaler_features = MinMaxScaler()
scaler_target = MinMaxScaler()
features_scaled = scaler_features.fit_transform(features)
target_scaled = scaler_target.fit_transform(target)

# Create time series dataset
def create_dataset(a, b, time_steps=1):
    X, Y = [], []
    for i in range(len(a) - time_steps):
        X.append(a[i:i + time_steps])
        Y.append(b[i + time_steps])
    return np.array(X), np.array(Y)

time_steps = 100 # Time steps for each sample 
a, b = create_dataset(features_scaled, target_scaled, time_steps)

# Split data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(a, b, test_size=0.2, shuffle=False)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Build the CNN model
model = Sequential([
    Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=3, activation='relu', input_shape=(time_steps, X.shape[2])),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=3, activation='relu'),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Flatten(),
    Dense(50, activation='relu'),
    Dense(1) 
])

model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Training and evaluation
history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_split=0.1, verbose=1)

# Make predictions
predictions = model.predict(X_test)

# Inverse transform the predictions and targets for comparison
Predicted_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(predictions)
Actual_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(y_test)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(Actual_Values, color ='blue',label='Actual Close Price')
plt.plot(Predicted_Values, color ='red',label='Predicted Close Price')
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel('AMZN Closing Price')
plt.legend()
plt.title('AMZN Closing Price Prediction (Daily Data)')
plt.show()
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Metrics Evaluation
mae = mean_absolute_error(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
mape = mean_absolute_percentage_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values)
r2_Score = r2_score(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
rmse =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values))

metrics = {
    'Metric': ['Mean Absolute Error', 'Root Mean Squared Error', 'Mean Absolute Percentage Error', 'R2 Score'],
    'Value': [f'{mae:.2f}', f'{rmse:.2f}', f'{(mape*100):.2f}%', f'{r2_Score:.2f}']
}
metrics_Table = pd.DataFrame(metrics)
print(metrics_Table)

# Data
data = pd.read_csv('/Users/aliabouyahia/Downloads/Data/BLK-Daily.csv') 

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Extract features and target + normalisation for CNN
features = data[['Open', 'High', 'Low']].values
target = data[['Close']].shift(-1).fillna(method='ffill').values  # Predict the next day's close , null values are filled using forward filling method 

scaler_features = MinMaxScaler()
scaler_target = MinMaxScaler()
features_scaled = scaler_features.fit_transform(features)
target_scaled = scaler_target.fit_transform(target)

# Create time series dataset
def create_dataset(a, b, time_steps=1):
    X, Y = [], []
    for i in range(len(a) - time_steps):
        X.append(a[i:i + time_steps])
        Y.append(b[i + time_steps])
    return np.array(X), np.array(Y)

time_steps = 100 # Time steps for each sample 
a, b = create_dataset(features_scaled, target_scaled, time_steps)

# Split data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(a, b, test_size=0.2, shuffle=False)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Build the CNN model
model = Sequential([
    Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=3, activation='relu', input_shape=(time_steps, X.shape[2])),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=3, activation='relu'),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Flatten(),
    Dense(50, activation='relu'),
    Dense(1) 
])

model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Training and evaluation
history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_split=0.1, verbose=1)

# Make predictions
predictions = model.predict(X_test)

# Inverse transform the predictions and targets for comparison
Predicted_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(predictions)
Actual_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(y_test)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(Actual_Values, color ='blue',label='Actual Close Price')
plt.plot(Predicted_Values, color ='red',label='Predicted Close Price')
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel('BLK Closing Price')
plt.legend()
plt.title('BLK Closing Price Prediction (Daily Data)')
plt.show()
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Metrics Evaluation
mae = mean_absolute_error(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
mape = mean_absolute_percentage_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values)
r2_Score = r2_score(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
rmse =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values))

}
metrics_Table = pd.DataFrame(metrics)
print(metrics_Table)

# Data
data = pd.read_csv('/Users/aliabouyahia/Downloads/Data/BLK-Weekly.csv') 

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Extract features and target + normalisation for CNN
features = data[['Open', 'High', 'Low']].values
target = data[['Close']].shift(-1).fillna(method='ffill').values  # Predict the next day's close , null values are filled using forward filling method 

scaler_features = MinMaxScaler()
scaler_target = MinMaxScaler()
features_scaled = scaler_features.fit_transform(features)
target_scaled = scaler_target.fit_transform(target)

# Create time series dataset
def create_dataset(a, b, time_steps=1):
    X, Y = [], []
    for i in range(len(a) - time_steps):
        X.append(a[i:i + time_steps])
        Y.append(b[i + time_steps])
    return np.array(X), np.array(Y)

time_steps = 100 # Time steps for each sample 
a, b = create_dataset(features_scaled, target_scaled, time_steps)

# Split data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(a, b, test_size=0.2, shuffle=False)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Build the CNN model
model = Sequential([
    Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=3, activation='relu', input_shape=(time_steps, X.shape[2])),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=3, activation='relu'),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Flatten(),
    Dense(50, activation='relu'),
    Dense(1) 
])

model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Training and evaluation
history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_split=0.1, verbose=1)

# Make predictions
predictions = model.predict(X_test)

# Inverse transform the predictions and targets for comparison
Predicted_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(predictions)
Actual_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(y_test)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(Actual_Values, color ='blue',label='Actual Close Price')
plt.plot(Predicted_Values, color ='red',label='Predicted Close Price')
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel('BLK Closing Price')
plt.legend()
plt.title('BLK Closing Price Prediction (Weekly Data)')
plt.show()
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Metrics Evaluation
mae = mean_absolute_error(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
mape = mean_absolute_percentage_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values)
r2_Score = r2_score(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
rmse =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values))

metrics = {
    'Metric': ['Mean Absolute Error', 'Root Mean Squared Error', 'Mean Absolute Percentage Error', 'R2 Score'],
    'Value': [f'{mae:.2f}', f'{rmse:.2f}', f'{(mape*100):.2f}%', f'{r2_Score:.2f}']
}
metrics_Table = pd.DataFrame(metrics)
print(metrics_Table)

# Data
data = pd.read_csv('/Users/aliabouyahia/Downloads/Data/JPM-Weekly.csv') 

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Extract features and target + normalisation for CNN
features = data[['Open', 'High', 'Low']].values
target = data[['Close']].shift(-1).fillna(method='ffill').values  # Predict the next day's close , null values are filled using forward filling method 

scaler_features = MinMaxScaler()
scaler_target = MinMaxScaler()
features_scaled = scaler_features.fit_transform(features)
target_scaled = scaler_target.fit_transform(target)

# Create time series dataset
def create_dataset(a, b, time_steps=1):
    X, Y = [], []
    for i in range(len(a) - time_steps):
        X.append(a[i:i + time_steps])
        Y.append(b[i + time_steps])
    return np.array(X), np.array(Y)

time_steps = 100 # Time steps for each sample 
a, b = create_dataset(features_scaled, target_scaled, time_steps)

# Split data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(a, b, test_size=0.2, shuffle=False)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Build the CNN model
model = Sequential([
    Conv1D(filters=64, kernel_size=3, activation='relu', input_shape=(time_steps, X.shape[2])),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Conv1D(filters=128, kernel_size=3, activation='relu'),
    MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2),
    Flatten(),
    Dense(50, activation='relu'),
    Dense(1) 
])

model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Training and evaluation
history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=50, batch_size=32, validation_split=0.1, verbose=1)

# Make predictions
predictions = model.predict(X_test)

# Inverse transform the predictions and targets for comparison
Predicted_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(predictions)
Actual_Values = scaler_target.inverse_transform(y_test)

#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(Actual_Values, color ='blue',label='Actual Close Price')
plt.plot(Predicted_Values, color ='red',label='Predicted Close Price')
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel('JPM Closing Price')
plt.legend()
plt.title('JPM Closing Price Prediction (Weekly Data)')
plt.show()
#----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Metrics Evaluation
mae = mean_absolute_error(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
mape = mean_absolute_percentage_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values)
r2_Score = r2_score(Actual_Values, Predicted_Values)
rmse =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(Actual_Values,Predicted_Values))

metrics = {
    'Metric': ['Mean Absolute Error', 'Root Mean Squared Error', 'Mean Absolute Percentage Error', 'R2 Score'],
    'Value': [f'{mae:.2f}', f'{rmse:.2f}', f'{(mape*100):.2f}%', f'{r2_Score:.2f}']
}
metrics_Table = pd.DataFrame(metrics)
print(metrics_Table)
